@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@token =
@gymId =
@studentId =

### 0) Health
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### 1) Crear Gym (publico)
POST {{baseUrl}}/gyms
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Titan Gym",
  "logoUrl": "https://example.com/logo.png",
  "primaryColor": "#111111",
  "secondaryColor": "#eeeeee"
}

### Copia el id y pégalo en @gymId arriba

### 2) Register (publico)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "owner1@titangym.com",
  "password": "12345678",
  "name": "Owner 1",
  "gymId": "{{gymId}}"
}

### Copia access_token y pégalo en @token arriba

### 3) Login (publico)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "owner1@titangym.com",
  "password": "12345678"
}

### 4) Auth me (protegido)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5) Students list (protegido)
GET {{baseUrl}}/students
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6) Create student (protegido)
POST {{baseUrl}}/students
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Juan Perez",
  "email": "juan@example.com",
  "phone": "123456789",
  "gymId": "{{gymId}}"
}

### Copia id y pégalo en @studentId arriba

### 7) Get student (protegido)
GET {{baseUrl}}/students/{{studentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8) Update student (protegido)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/students/{{studentId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "phone": "999999999"
}

### 9) Delete student (protegido)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/students/{{studentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 10) Gyms list (protegido por OWNER/ADMIN)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gyms
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 11) Delete gym (protegido)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/gyms/{{gymId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 11) Security test: sin token debe dar 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/students